pros:
* Great people to work with most of whom are very smart, supportive, and respectful. More of a tight-knit feel than the bulge brackets;

* Strong senior management who are constantly engaged and visible. They genuinely care and support their employees;

* Above industry compensation;

cons:
* company lacks diversity in the upper echelon of management (company is actively working to improve that);

* the strive for excellence and being "elite" creates a demanding and intense work environment (typical of any Wall Street firm);

* Upward mobility gets tougher as you climb the ladder given the company's preference to recruit top senior talent than promote from within.
